# ClaimsOS – Project Intelligence

## Critical Patterns

### Backend
- All services are plain Python classes instantiated directly (no FastAPI DI for services, only for repositories)
- `ClaimsRepository` is the central persistence class — it also builds provider context and insights
- Claims are **upserted** on `claim_id` — re-processing the same ID updates the record
- `_run_claim_processing()` in `claims.py` router is the canonical pipeline function — all three intake paths (JSON, X12, document) funnel through it
- `ensure_tenant()` and `ensure_provider_for_tenant()` auto-provision records on first encounter — never assume they exist
- `execute_with_retry()` wraps all Supabase calls — always use it, never call `.execute()` directly
- Agent chat always returns HTTP 200 — never raise 4xx for question failures

### Frontend
- All application state lives in `App.tsx` — no Redux, no Zustand, no React Router
- View switching is via `activeView` state variable (type `ViewId`) — conditional rendering, not routing
- All API calls are made from `App.tsx` handler functions and passed as props to page components
- The `AgentChatWidget` is rendered outside `AppShell` so it floats over all views

### Design System ("Surgical Ledger")
- Base surface: `#F7F9FB` (surface), containers: `#F0F4F7` (low), `#FFFFFF` (lowest/focus)
- Primary action color: `#0053DC` (secondary) — use gradient `#0053DC` → `#0049C2` for CTAs
- **NEVER use 1px borders for structural sectioning** — use tonal background shifts instead
- **NEVER use full rounded pills** — use 4px (DEFAULT) or 6px (md) border radius
- **NEVER use #000000** — use `#2A3439` (on-surface) for text
- Fonts: Manrope for headlines/display, Inter for data/UI
- Status chips: `primary-container` for neutral, `error-container` for denials
- Glassmorphism for floating modals: `surface-container-lowest` at 85% opacity + 12px backdrop-blur

## Domain Knowledge

### Claim Processing Rules
- Straight-through approval requires: POS=11, single service line, amount ≤ $250
- Amount > $1000 triggers hard denial guardrail
- Provider ID starting with "ZZ" = eligibility mismatch (test pattern)
- HMO plans require referral for specialist codes: 99244, 99245, 27447, 93000
- Prior auth required codes: 27447, 29881, 45385, 70553
- Required modifiers: 93000 needs modifier 25, 29881 needs modifier 59
- Supported CPT/ICD pairs (8 total): E11.9/99213, I10/99213, J02.9/99213, M54.5/97110, M17.11/27447, M17.11/29881, R51.9/99214, I25.10/93000

### Confidence Score Thresholds
- Human review triggered when: `confidence_score < 0.72` OR `outcome == "review"`
- Approve path: starts at 0.90, max ~0.98
- Review path: starts at 0.70, min 0.46
- Denial path: starts at 0.50, min 0.14

### Multi-Tenancy
- Tenant key is derived from payer name (slugified)
- Demo tenant: "Apex Health Plan" → tenant_key: "apex-health-plan"
- OpenAI vector store per tenant: `claimsos-policies-{tenant_key}`

## File Locations Quick Reference

### Backend Key Files
- Pipeline entry: `apps/api/app/api/v1/routes/claims.py` → `_run_claim_processing()`
- Claim models: `apps/api/app/domain/claims/models.py`
- Validation rules: `apps/api/app/domain/claims/validation_service.py`
- Adjudication checks: `apps/api/app/domain/claims/adjudication_service.py`
- Confidence scoring: `apps/api/app/domain/claims/confidence_service.py`
- Policy RAG: `apps/api/app/domain/policies/retrieval_service.py`
- X12 parser: `apps/api/app/domain/claims/x12_parser.py`
- Document intake: `apps/api/app/domain/claims/document_intake_service.py`
- Agent chat: `apps/api/app/domain/agent/service.py`
- Config: `apps/api/app/core/config.py`

### Frontend Key Files
- App state + routing: `apps/web/src/app/App.tsx`
- Claims API: `apps/web/src/shared/api/claims.ts`
- Intake page: `apps/web/src/features/intake/components/IntakePolicyPage.tsx`
- Adjudication page: `apps/web/src/features/adjudication/components/AdjudicationPage.tsx`
- Agent widget: `apps/web/src/features/agent/components/AgentChatWidget.tsx`
- App shell: `apps/web/src/shared/layout/AppShell.tsx` (or similar)

### Database Migrations
- `infra/supabase/001_initial_claimsos.sql` – Core claims tables
- `infra/supabase/002_tenant_provider_foundation.sql` – Tenants + providers
- `infra/supabase/003_policy_ingestion_foundation.sql` – Policy documents + chunks
- `infra/supabase/004_openai_vector_store_foundation.sql` – OpenAI vector store metadata
- `infra/supabase/005_detailed_claim_phase1.sql` – Extended claim fields
- `infra/supabase/006_members_foundation.sql` – Members table

### Sample Data
- Hero OCR scenario: `sample_data/claim_documents/APX-OCR-HERO-ORTHO-3001.*`
- Policy documents: `sample_data/policies/*.md`
- X12 batch: `sample_data/claims/apex_bulk_realistic_5_claims.x12`
- JSON scenarios: `sample_data/claims/internal_json/advanced/*.json`

## Build & Run Commands
```bash
# Backend
cd apps/api && uvicorn app.main:app --reload

# Frontend
cd apps/web && npm run dev

# Frontend build check
cd apps/web && npm run build
```

